(57, 1, 1, 47, 1, 1, 1, 'Timothy our brother', 'Connection of Paul and Timothy', 'Both passages emphasize Paul and Timothy as key figures in their respective letters. They are introduced as brothers, highlighting their partnership in ministry.', 'parallel', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(57, 1, 1, 49, 4, 1, 1, 'prisoner of Jesus Christ', 'Connection of Paul as Prisoner', 'Both passages emphasize Paul’s status as a prisoner, linking his circumstances to his call for believers to live in a manner worthy of their calling. This connection highlights the theme of suffering for the faith and the responsibility that comes with it.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(57, 1, 2, 50, 2, 25, 25, 'fellowsoldier', 'Fellowsoldier Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the term ''fellowsoldier,'' highlighting a shared commitment to ministry and labor in the faith. This connection illustrates the camaraderie and support among early Christian workers.', 'keyword', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
